      "step_index": 6,
      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 3) MECHANISTIC BASIS (how it could bind hERG)\nMost small-molecule hERG blockers bind in the **inner cavity** of the channel (open/inactivated states), often involving:\n- **Cation\u2013\u03c0 / electrostatic interactions** between the protonated amine and aromatic residues lining the pore (classically discussed around Tyr/Phe residues),\n- **\u03c0\u2013\u03c0 and hydrophobic contacts** from aromatic rings.",
