      "content": "## 5) VERIFICATION / UNCERTAINTY CHECK (alternative explanations)\n- **Could it be negative?** Yes, if overall **lipophilicity is low** (ester + heteroaromatic [nH] + only one aromatic ring) and the **geometry/spacing** doesn\u2019t match the cavity pharmacophore well, it might have **minimal** hERG inhibition.\n- **Could it be strongly positive?** Less likely: it lacks the **large hydrophobic substituents** and **extended architecture** often seen in potent blockers; also the amine is **primary** (many very potent hERG blockers are tertiary, though primary can still bind).\n- No glaring \u201cterfenadine-like\u201d alert; so if it blocks, it may be **moderate/weak** rather than high potency.",
